<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10627150>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A-G. Trichocline maxima. A. General view of the species habit; B. Capitulum; C. Involucre; D. Detail of achene and pappus; E. Detail of rosette leaves, scapes and xylopodium; F. Detail of the rosette and lobate leaves; G. Habitat. Photos credits: A-C, F and G by José M. Bonifacino; D by Fábio P. Torchelsen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10627150/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10627152>
    dc:description "Figure 2. A-E. Illustration of Trichocline maxima. A. Habit; B. Outer to inner phyllaries; C. Ray florets; D. Disc florets; E. Achene.Illustrations A–E were made by Edson Luis de Carvalho Soares and adapted from Pasini & Ritter (2012). José M. Bonifacino drew the illustration of the achene E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10627152/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10627154>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Distribution map of Trichocline maxima. The orange dot represents the latest record of the species that is reported in this work. The black dot in Uruguay is from collections cited in the additional examined material section. The black dot in Brazil represents the possible location of Malme’s (1931) citation of a Sellow’s collection: Inter Rio Pardo et Bagé." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10627154/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

